Sophie's Choice is a 1982 American drama film directed by Alan J. Pakula, who adapted the novel of the same name by William Styron. Meryl Streep stars as Sophie, a Polish immigrant who shares a boarding house in Brooklyn with her tempestuous lover (Kevin Kline) and a young writer (Peter MacNicol).Streep's performance was commended, and it won her the Academy Award for Best Actress. The film was nominated for Best Cinematography (NÃ©stor Almendros), Costume Design (Albert Wolsky), Best Music (Marvin Hamlisch), and Best Writing, Screenplay Based on Material from Another Medium (Alan J. Pakula).British company ITC Entertainment produced the film, and Lew Grade was influential in bringing the novel to the big screen.[citation needed]
